<div id="review_1748822360" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1748822360" />
    <a title="Chris" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23636733-chris"><img alt="Chris" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1465247332p2/23636733.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1748822360?book_show_action=true">Oct 12, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chris" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chris" href="/user/show/23636733-chris">Chris</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/31822076-luces-en-el-mar">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Chris by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/48503940-florentina">Florentina</a>
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1748822360" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13078460316443706898">This book was suggested to me and I was quick to start reading. I&apos;m always looking for a great new book written in Spanish, and on reading the summary I was immediately interested. The way the book is written keeps you interested the entire time, I can&apos;t remember a point where I wasn&apos;t completely lost in the story. And as the story progressed I found my self agreeing more and more with the lessons that Los Señores Grapes learn as well as the profundity of their meanings. While reading I couldn&apos;t</span>
  <span id="freeText13078460316443706898" style="display:none">This book was suggested to me and I was quick to start reading. I'm always looking for a great new book written in Spanish, and on reading the summary I was immediately interested. The way the book is written keeps you interested the entire time, I can't remember a point where I wasn't completely lost in the story. And as the story progressed I found my self agreeing more and more with the lessons that Los Señores Grapes learn as well as the profundity of their meanings. While reading I couldn't help but be reminded of The Alchemist at times. It's obvious that the writer is experienced in life as well as in writing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13078460316443706898" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review1748822360">
